This paper deals with image deconvolution using deep generative networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an alternating gradient descent scheme, which involves optimization techniques commonly used in machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper deals with image datasets, which is a topic in computer graphics (GR) and multimedia (MM).
